    <h2 class="wow fadeInDown">History</h2>
 <p style="text-align:justify">India is a sovereign, socialist and democratic country where the rights of every citizen are equal in the eyes of the law. Any form of atrocity/ discrimination based on the sex, caste, creed, religious belief etc. is a punishable offence in the eyes of the law. Despite all the laws in place, there is a sharp increase in crimes committed, including the denial of some of the basic rights to the very citizen of the independent India. Unfortunately due to the slow progress of the cases, the criminals get encouraged and challenging the law in the country in every nook and corner and level of atrocities is escalating like anything.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify">A group of few young, dynamic and energetic officers with progressive thinking were pained to see the inhuman treatment meted to human beings on a sustained basis on these grounds of discrimination. Not only the inhuman treatment but many of the victims lost their life as well due to discrimination.  Seeing a series of such incidences in succession, the group of progressive officers from different walks of life, especially after Dangawas Village incident, decided to join hands in fighting the menace of inhuman treatment, merely based on caste, creed, religion, sex, etc. and for bringing parity in the society in the overall national interest. <strong>This group of officers helped in forming of the trust, which they felt was inevitable.</strong> The objectives of the trust are many including assistance to the people/victims of such inhuman treatment. The group realized the need to eradicate this inhuman behavior from the society by reaching to the grassroots of the problem and therefore having realized the weaknesses of those who suffered, the group of such likeminded officers decided to contribute <%--on monthly basis to--%> enable people from the weaker strata of the society to make them economically self-sufficient, educated to avert injustice and to eradicate the atrocity menace. Thus, it would not only remove the blot of inhuman treatment in the Indian society but would be a great service to the mankind and our nation as well. </p>
    
